The paper deals with the problem of designing revenue optimal auctions, which is a classic topic in algorithmic game theory (cs.GT). The solution involves a maximum weight independent set problem, which is a fundamental problem in combinatorial optimization (cs.DS). The paper also uses probability distributions to model the buyers' valuations, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and economics (cs.EC). Finally, the paper involves optimization and information theory, which are relevant to the sub-category of information theory (cs.IT).
